<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Philippines-Sinking     10-15 0116</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Philippines-Sinking,0118</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>More Than 50 Drown in Ferry Sinking</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CEBU CITY, Philippines (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A small, overloaded ferry boat
sank in heavy seas in the central Philippines, and at least 55
people drowned, the Coast Guard reported today. It said 77 were
rescued.
   The vessel is authorized to carry 92 people. Officials did not
say if they had accounted for everyone who had been on board.
   The 35-ton motor boat met a wind gust and big waves before
sinking off the southern tip of Samar island early Friday, the
Coast Guard report said.
   The boat, which left the town of Giporlos, was bound for
Tacloban city on the neighboring island of Leyte, the report said.
</TEXT>
