<TEXT>
   About 200 leftist guerrillas marched
into a town and shot and killed two civilians, the army said.
   The attack by the National Liberation Army took place Friday in
Macaravita, a town of 7,000 people about 150 miles northeast of the
capital of Bogota, the army communique said.
