<HEAD>Rain in the Northwest, Southwest, Midwest</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Light rain and showers fell over the Pacific Northwest today as
showers and thunderstorms diminished over sections of Arizona.
   Scattered showers were over the southwest quarter of New Mexico,
scattered showers and a few thunderstorms were over the
mid-Mississippi Valley, and showers fell over northeast and central
Illinois and central and southwest Missouri.
   Numerous showers and thunderstorms fell over central and eastern
Arizona on Friday, producing heavy rain. Phoenix received 2\ inches
and Organ Pipe National Monument and Carefree got 2 inches. The
precipitation diminished late Friday.
   Today's forecast called for scattered showers and thunderstorms
from eastern Arizona to southwest Texas, and widely scattered
showers over southern Florida, Washington state and from the
mountains of western Montana to western Wyoming.
   Temperatures were forecast to reach the 50s from northeast New
York state to northern New England, with some readings in the 40s
in northern Maine; the 80s in southern Florida, the central and
southern Great Plains and from the desert Southwest to interior
valleys of northern and central California; and in the 60s and 70s
elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 30
degrees at Limestone, Maine, to 75 degrees at the Naval Air Station
near Corpus Christi, Texas.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 50 fair; Boston 48 fair; Buffalo 50 fair;
Charleston, S.C. 45 foggy; Cincinnati 53 fair; Cleveland 51 cloudy;
Detroit 56 cloudy; Miami 68 partly cloudy; New York 48 fair;
Philadelphia 43 fair; Pittsburgh 47 fair; Portland, Maine 46
cloudy; Washington 46 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 46 fair; Chicago 61 partly cloudy;
Dallas-Fort Worth 79 fair; Denver 61 cloudy; Des Moines 61 fair;
Indianapolis 54 fair; Kansas City 65 windy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 54
fair; Nashville 48 fair; New Orleans 52 fair; St. Louis 66 cloudy.
   _West: Albuquerque 58 cloudy; Anchorage 24 fair; Las Vegas 68
fair; Los Angeles 63 fair; Phoenix 65 fair; Salt Lake City 50 fair;
San Diego 64 fair; San Francisco 55 fair; Seattle 57 rain.
   _Canada: Montreal 48 cloudy; Toronto 46 fair.
</TEXT>
