<HEAD>278 Die of Encephalitis</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 270 people throughout Nepal
have died of encephalitis in the past two months, Health Ministry
officials said Saturday.
   Officials said 278 of the 899 people diagnosed with the viral
disease had died. Another 170 are undergoing treatment, and others
have been cured, the ministry said.
   Most of the affected areas lie in the tropical plains of
southern Nepal bordering northern and eastern Indian states of
Uttar Pradesh, Bihar and Bengal.
   The disease is transmitted from animals to human beings by
mosquitoes.
