<HEAD>LaserPhoto NY14</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN ANTONIO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mayor Henry Cisneros said he will try
to serve out the remaining months of his fourth term with dignity
after acknowledging a close, personal relationship with a woman
outside his marriage.
   Cisneros, 41, a popular Hispanic leader once considered a
potential Democratic vice presidential candidate, talked to
reporters Friday after a newspaper article detailed his
relationship with Linda Medlar, 39.
   Mrs. Medlar, who has helped the mayor in various fund-raising
campaigns, was quoted in a front-page column in Friday's San
Antonio Express-News as calling the mayor ``love of my life'' and
saying they ``hope to be able to live out the rest of our lives
together.''
   Mrs. Medlar is married to the co-owner of a jewelry store.
   Cisneros said Friday he wants to work out his marital problems
to protect his wife of 19 years, Mary Alice, and his teen-age
daughters and young son. He declined to elaborate on his
relationship with Mrs. Medlar, but said it was not the major
problem between him and his wife.
   ``I am saying that I am a human being in addition to being
mayor,'' Cisneros said. ``That I am not perfect and that I have
various kinds of needs of friendship and support.''
   Cisneros has announced he won't seek re-election when his term
expires in May or run for state office in 1990.
</TEXT>
